    "history": {
        "short_description": "A famous dam and garden complex built in 1955, known for boating, ropeway rides, and landscaped gardens.",
        "detailed": "Malampuzha Dam, completed in 1955 across the Malampuzha tributary of Bharathapuzha, is one of Kerala’s earliest and largest irrigation projects. The beautifully designed Malampuzha Gardens were developed soon after to promote tourism. The iconic Yakshi sculpture by Kanayi Kunhiraman, the Rock Garden made with recycled materials, and the aerial ropeway make this destination one of the most visited family attractions in Palakkad."
    },
